'''AH Competições''' (previously known as '''WB Motorsport''') is a [[Brazil]]ian [[auto racing]] team founded in 1996 by [[Stock Car Brasil]] co-founder Washington Bezerra and former racing driver [[Wilson Fittipaldi]]. The team won the championship in [[Stock Car Brasil]], [[Campeonato Brasileiro de Turismo|Stock Car Light]] and [[Campeonato Brasileiro de GT|Brazilian GT Championship]]. In 2010 the team was renamed for AH Competições with former racing driver Antonio Hermann became the team owner alongside Bezerra. In 2013 the team joined [[FIA GT Series]] with [[BMW]] under the name '''BMW Sports Trophy Team Brasil'''.

