{{orphan|date=December 2016}}
'''Gary Al-Smith''' is a [[Ghana]]ian sports journalist who reports locally and for international media – with a focus on African football.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/profile/gary-al-smith|title=Gary Al-Smith|website=the Guardian|access-date=2016-12-23}}</ref> He is also a [[Global Shapers|global shaper]] and a [[UNICEF]] ambassador.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.globalshapers.org/shapers/gary-al-smith|title=Gary Al-Smith {{!}} Global Shapers Community|website=www.globalshapers.org|access-date=2016-12-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ocsportsnews.com/unicef-ghana-appoints-gary-al-smith-on-a-water-project/|title=UNICEF Ghana appoints Gary Al-Smith on a water project.|newspaper=OC SPORTS NEWS|language=en-us|access-date=2016-12-23}}</ref> He initially worked with [[Citi FM (Ghana)|Citi FM]] however moved and is currently with [[Joy FM (Ghana)|Joy FM]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://enewsgh.com/2015/01/10/exclusive-joy-fm-pays-almost-ghc-100-000-for-gary-al-smith-joins-after-afcon/|title=EXCLUSIVE! Joy FM pays almost GHC 100, 000 for Gary Al-Smith... joins after AFCON{{!}} ENewsGh|date=2015-01-10|website=Proudly Ghanaian! {{!}} ENewsGh|access-date=2016-12-23}}</ref> He does stories for [[The Guardian|Guardian]], [[BBC]], [[CNN]], the [[The New York Times|New York Times]] and [[SuperSport (South African TV channel)|SuperSport]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.myjoyonline.com/news/2016/January-4th/full-list-joy-fms-manasseh-azure-gary-al-smith-join-anas-as-2015-ghanas-most-influential.php|title=FULL LIST: Joy FM's Manasseh Azure, Gary Al-Smith join Anas among 2015 Ghana's Most Influential - MyJoyOnline|last=Myjoyonline.com|website=www.myjoyonline.com|access-date=2016-12-23}}</ref><ref name=":0" />

